external_knowledge:
- "seeds of creativity" refers to the games;
- "garden of games" refers to the collection of games available;
- "gardeners and caretakers" refer to the designers and publishers;
- "sweetness of the fruit they bore" refers to the average rating of the games;
- The earliest year is the year with the minimum value in the `year` column of the `games` table.

- 'secret gardens of creativity' metaphorically refers to a collection of creative works, here specifically games;
- 'born in lands beyond the digital millennium' is a poetic way of saying games released after the year 2000;
- 'fertile minds of designers sown before the 1980s' refers to designers born before 1980;
- 'environments where English flowers are the language of choice' signifies games that are language-dependent on English;
- 'publishers emerging post-2000 in the United States' means publishers founded after 2000 with headquarters in the US;
- 'blossomed beautifully with average and geek ratings above the celestial number 8' means games with ratings over 8;
- 'attract pollinators in droves with over 50 votes' indicates games that have received more than 50 votes.

- "golden apples of knowledge" refers to games that are educational or enlightening;
- "dawn of the second decade" refers to the year 2010;
- "no more than an hour to savor" means games with a play time of 60 minutes or less;
- "young minds" refers to children aged 10 or younger;
- "crafted by at least two artists" means the game has at least two designers;
- "distinct flavors" refers to different mechanics incorporated in the game;
- "most celebrated by players" means games with the highest average rating.

sql:
SELECT name
FROM games
WHERE avg_rating > 8.0;

SELECT game_id, name, min_players, max_players, min_age, complexity
FROM games
WHERE min_players = (
    SELECT MIN(min_players) FROM games
)
AND max_players = (
    SELECT MAX(max_players) FROM games
)
AND min_age = (
    SELECT MIN(min_age) FROM games
)
AND complexity = (
    SELECT MAX(complexity) FROM games
);

SELECT name 
FROM games
WHERE avg_rating = (SELECT MAX(avg_rating) FROM games);

SELECT username, email, role
FROM users
WHERE role = 'regular';
